name: Area U:  The Ruins of Berez
caption:
I had nothing left to give but my own life’s blood, but it was hers to take. She would at last be my bride.

— Strahd von Zarovich
in I, Strahd: The Memoirs of a Vampire
description: The ruins of Berez are now home to Baba Lysaga (see appendix D), an almost mythic figure tied to Strahd’s ancient past. A hermit, she spends most of her time crafting and animating scarecrows to hunt down and kill the ravens and the wereravens that infest Strahd’s domain. When she isn’t working evil magic, Baba Lysaga sacrifices beasts to Mother Night and collects their blood, then bathes in the blood on nights of the new moon in a ritual to stave off the effects of extreme old age.
